5:
Sorry to keep you waiting. I got our
next job.
8: What were you guys talking about?
11:
Just a rumor. Apparently there's a
woman who shows up outta
nowhere and guides lost
adventurers out of the Kaleidoscope.
16:
What, just like that? Such a feat
doesn't sound possible.
19:
Which is why I called it a rumor. No
way it's true.
21:
When you add in the supposed
floating lamps that appear and lead
you to her, it starts sounding like a
complete fairy tale.
24:
Hmm... It would certainly be
interesting if it were true though.
28:
I'd rather we DIDN'T meet her,
considering she only shows up when
people are lost.
34:
Ugh, think I'm reaching my limit
here...
38:
Save the chatter, we need to hurry.
The tremors are getting worse!
46:
Get up! We don't have much time
before we're hit by a distortion!
49:
Th-this is my first time in the
midways! I wasn't ready for this!
53:
Nimbus, grab him and go! I'll clear
the way!
58: Alk, you need to get a move on!
79:
Shoot, that's right. I was in the
Kaleidoscope... and then I got swept
up in the distortion!
85:
Can't see or hear a thing here. What
is this place?
88:
The heck? Am I supposed to follow
after?
93:
Been walking a while now... Was this
really such a good idea?
95:
Yeah, it was! You're in good hands
now.
99:
You don't seem injured. Glad to see
you didn't run into any trouble on
the way.
108:
I am Firamelia, adventurer and
Kaleidoscope surveyor.
110:
I also help guide lost adventurers to
safety whenever I can. I hope you're
ready for some more walking.
114:
I guess I don't really have a choice,
huh... I'm Alk. Nice to meet you.
118:
Alk, hmm? That's a nice name.
Anyway, let's get going.
123:
Mind telling me exactly where we're
headed? It's just pitch black
darkness no matter where I look.
126:
Why, outside, of course. Just follow
after me, and everything will be fine.
131:
I am so lost in more than one way
right now...
135:
So you helped out a fellow
adventurer in trouble and got swept
away...
137:
While that kind of compassion is
commendable, you shouldn't make
a habit of endangering yourself.
143:
By the way, are you sure we're
walking toward an exit? Everything
still looks the same to me...
146:
Don't you worry about a thing. I
always know where the correct path
is.
151:
W-wait, is that the exit? Incredible,
you actually found it!
155:
Oh, that's not the exit. I've never seen
this type of pathway before.
162:
Hmmm... It feels a little strange, but
not dangerous.
164:
It should be fine to go through. Let's
try it.
168:
Hold on a minute! That is the least
reassuring thing you could've said!
174:
Starview Village... I actually made it
home!
183:
Is it truly you? Are you hurt? Hungry?
Actually alive and not a zombie?
189:
Where the hell have you been?! How
could you leave us hangin' for 3
whole days!
193:
It's not like I wasn't trying to get
back—
Did... Did you just say 3 days?!
197:
No way! What? It's only been like 2
hours for me, I swear!
202:
...Hmm, I think the path we took was
a little more dangerous than I
thought. I should probably avoid
using it again.
206:
So you have the power to know the
correct path forward... It is truly
amazing you were able to find an
exit at all.
208:
We are forever in your debt,
Firamelia. Alk wouldn't have made it
home without you.
211:
I'm afraid it was more luck this time
that guided us. I've never
experienced a time warp before.
214:
But I suppose in the end, I was able
to partake in a fine meal and arrive
in a wonderful town, so it all worked
out.
219: Nothing much affects you, does it?
223:
Yeah, she's a force to be reckoned
with...
227:
There's something I've been
meaning to ask. Is it true that this
town is only accessible to people
Stella allows in?
232:
Uh, partially? Sometimes we get
people who accidentally wander in,
kind of like we did.
236:
...Fate must have brought me here
then. This works out perfectly.
238:
Would you allow me to live in
Starview? I'll pay rent, of course.
242:
You're more than welcome to! Right,
Stella?
247:
Indeed. Our home is open to you,
Firamelia.
251:
Hehe, you guys seem like a fun
bunch. Thanks for having me.
